heading: Folklore. [State, country, region, continent, etc.].
general-note: Here are entered single folktales or collections of folklore originating in a particular geographic area. Single folktales or collections of folklore of ethnic groups are entered under the heading for the group with the subdivision Folklore and are given a second heading for the folklore of the appropriate geographic area, e.g. 1. Ashanti (African people)--Folklore. 2. Folklore--Ghana; 1. Navajo Indians--Folklore. 2. Folklore--Southwest, New..
